	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Here is what I would like to see changed.<BR>
<BR>
First, the length of time to answer petitions.   It needs to be shortened or at least stated when you do the petition.   Even a calm, polite person can get really irate after being made to wait 5 hours only to get the standard &quot;when can't help you&quot; line.<BR>
<BR>
Second, it appears that when there is any possible way the CS can be exploited, there is a new CS rule that prevents a GM from offering any help on the topic regardless of the situation.   I realize that many people probably fradulently contact the CS staff regarding rez and reimbursement, but what about the people that don't.   Honest players shouldn't be denied help just because others have burned the CS team in the past.   Not to mention, what is the big deal anyways?   If someone gets a rez because they lost their character due to a reasonible server side bug I hardly think that would start a riot among the other players who felt that the person got an unfair advantage.   They aren't getting any more experience than they already had, they are just getting back what they lost.   If I saw a GM give someone a rez I would send the GM a /cheer.<BR>
<BR>
Once when we were playing in Sol A my friend died in the lava and we could not find her corpse.   A GM just happened to be in the zone at the time and I sent her a tell stating what happened.   Immediately she came and got the corpse to the zone for us, no questions asked.   That was a positive experience with a GM, and I am greatful to this day for that kind CS.   We continued the remainder of our evening having fun playing the game, it could have gone the other way.<BR>
<BR>
Another time I got my corpse stuck in a mountain somehow when I died, I could not get it back.   I petitioned and 3 hours later was told that I needed to have a necro summon it for me.   What makes the CS staff assume that a level 20 player (which I was at the time) knows high level necros that can do that let alone have the pp to afford such a service.    Anyhow, I was stuck for days until a friend of a friend found someone to summon it for me.   That is not good CS, I was very angry and concerned I was not going to get my character back.  Not to mentioned very upset that I had to wait 3 hours to hear that I wasn't going to get help.   People don't have unlimited amount of time to just sit around waiting to hear back from a GM.  What difference would it have made if the GM could have just summoned it to a location that I could have got it at?   Nobody would have known the difference and they would have had a very happy customer.   Instead everyone I knew heard about yet one more instance of useless GM assistance.<BR>
<BR>
Lastly, guides.   If you are going to have guides then at least make them provide some sort of usefulness.   I have nothing against the guides and found most of them to be friendly people,  but from the sound of it they can't do anything to help anyone.   If the GM staff is bogged down with requests to the point that it takes up to 5 hours to reply then send some of the work to the guides.   I am sure guides would rather help people than to give there &quot;I can't help you, you need to talk to a GM&quot; line (I bet they have that hotkeyed).
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
